FBIS3-43441 "drafr005_c_94005" FBIS-AFR-94-005 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Jan 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Roundup of ANC Organization Activities SDU's Said Involved in Violence MB0701070994 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 0500 GMT 7 Jan 94 MB0701070994 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The defense force has said that members of Self-Defense Units [SDU] are involved in incidents of violence, making it difficult to establish peace and stability on the East Rand. The commander of the defense force's Group 41, Colonel C.P du Toit, said members of the SDU were intimidating residents and were in possession of illegal weapons. Earlier the ANC [African National Congress] appointed a commission of inquiry into the activities of the units. However, the Ministry of Law and Order believes that the Goldstone Commission should carry out the investigation.
